      "writtenOn": "2021-01-05T16:25:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Conceptually seems weird that `convertWhile` is public and roughly-equivalent functions like `convertDo` are private. Does this eventually get sorted out and make more sense? Or are we just making things public on a case-by-case basis based on what the DSL needs to use?\n\nIdeally I\u0027d like to be able to have a mental model for which things should be public and private in the IRGenerator. Or we could just make the DSL classes friends since they are basically IR generators anyway.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 173,
        "startChar": 31,
        "endLine": 173,
        "endChar": 43
      },
      "revId": "a0cd4c7fefc2646776049ce303bdc580f35ee95e",
